casebody.data:
Cuyahoga County Bar Association v. Gonzalez. Cuyahoga County Bar Association v. Stafford.

[Cite as Cuyahoga Cty. Bar Assn. v. Gonzalez (2000), 89 Ohio St.3d 470.]

(Nos. 00-412 and 00-413 Submitted April 26, 2000 Decided August 16, 2000.) Howard A. Shulman and Lester S. Potash, for relator. Wesley A. Dumas, for respondent Gonzalez. Charles W. Kettlewell, for respondent Stafford. *471 Per Curiam.

We adopt the findings, conclusions, and recommendations of the board. Respondent Gonzalez and respondent Stafford are hereby publicly reprimanded. Costs of these proceedings are taxed equally to each respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
